{
  "stem": "25651.15",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I recall, there was a big advertisement as you walked into the airport from the customs hall, there was a big advertisement of the map of Germany, the way it used to be-- you know, the Great Reich under Hitler.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it said-- the advertisement said, av drie Teile geteitl, nie.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Divided into three parts, never.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the three parts was West Germany, East Germany, and then the Oder-Neisse part, which Poland took away.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I always looked at that, and I thought to myself, let it stay the way it is, you know, divided.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Germany is better divided.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And now that I visit Czechoslovakia again, and I've got a bit of a better grasp of history-- since my retirement I have been doing more history than engineering.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In fact, I don't do any engineering.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I think to myself that the unification of Germany has been a wrong move.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the last reunion was '94. '90 was the first reunion.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And somehow the first reunion was a better atmosphere than the last one.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I advised on the last one that we should take a hotel in the countryside.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we should stay there for several days and just be amongst us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And there were three television crews that came because several other Birkenau Boys with their own initiatives arranged.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was terribly intrusive because people behave differently under the camera.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I felt that I wasn't getting through to, to people, you know, on a people level.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were all acting parts.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We're in this nice hotel in the countryside, but Tommy Frankel, for example, who is a Birkenau Boy, somehow smelled it, you know, what was going to happen.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He himself is a camera man and worked in, in TV.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
